universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Bear : obj
constant Cow : obj
constant Rabbit : obj
constant Dog : obj

constant Chases : obj → obj → Prop
constant Eats : obj → obj → Prop
constant Big : obj → Prop
constant Round : obj → Prop
constant Sees : obj → obj → Prop
constant Red : obj → Prop
constant Cold : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Chases Bear Cow
axiom T2 : Eats Bear Rabbit
axiom T3 : Big Bear
axiom T4 : Round Bear
axiom T5 : Sees Bear Cow
axiom T6 : Sees Bear Dog
axiom T7 : Eats Cow Rabbit
axiom T8 : Chases Dog Rabbit
axiom T9 : Eats Dog Rabbit
axiom T10 : Chases Rabbit Bear
axiom T11 : Chases Rabbit Cow
axiom T12 : Big Rabbit
axiom T13 : Red Rabbit
axiom T14 : Round Rabbit

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Bear → Cold x
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Eats x Rabbit → Round Rabbit
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Rabbit ∧ Chases Rabbit Cow → Eats Cow Bear
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Bear ∧ Chases x Dog → Eats Dog Bear
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Eats x Bear → Sees x Rabbit
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Rabbit ∧ Chases Rabbit Cow → Big x
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Dog ∧ Eats Dog Rabbit → Round Rabbit
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Chases x Bear → Eats x Bear

theorem cow_is_big : Big Cow :=
begin
  apply R6 Cow,
  split,
  exact T5,
  exact T11,
end

-- The answer is True
